Management TeamSynalloy’s Management and Board of Directors sincerely appreciate the support of our shareholders, customers and dedicated employees.




 




Craig C. Bram



Title: President and CEO
Email Address: CBram@Synalloy.com



Craig C. Bram became President and CEO in January 2011 and has been a Director of the Company since 2004.  He has over 30 years’ experience in business management, financial operations, logistics, management consulting, business start-ups and strategic planning for a variety of companies. Mr. Bram received his B.B.A. in Marketing from James Madison University, graduating Summa cum Laude. He also received his M.B.A. from Virginia Commonwealth University, with a concentration in Finance.








 




Dennis M. Loughran



Title: Senior Vice President & CFO
Email Address: DLoughran@Synalloy.com



Dennis M. Loughran joined the Company in July 2015 as Senior Vice President and Chief Financial Officer. His experience includes nineteen years with Reynolds Metals Company in various financial and operations roles and six years with Alcoa Consumer Products. More recently, he served eight years as the Chief Financial Officer for Rogers Corporation (NYSE:ROG)  He has a broad background in international business management, financial reporting, planning and analysis, profit improvement, mergers and acquisitions, supply chain optimization, tax and treasury management and investor relations.  Mr. Loughran attended the University of Richmond, where he was a scholarship athlete in football and attained a BS in Business Administration (Magna Cum Laude) with a major in Accounting. He also received his M.B.A. from Virginia Commonwealth University, with a concentration in Finance. He is a Certified Public Accountant.
 








 




Sally M. Cunningham



Email Address: SCunningham@Synalloy.com
Title: Vice President of Corporate Administration, Corporate Secretary



Sally M. Cunningham joined the Company in October 2015 as Vice President of Corporate Administration and Corporate Secretary. Prior to Synalloy, she was Vice President, Finance and Operations at ICF International (NYSE: ICFI). Ms. Cunningham has a broad background in business operations, administration, mergers and acquisitions and finance across a number of industries. Ms. Cunningham received her B.B.A. in Accounting from the College of William and Mary and her M.B.A. from the University of Richmond. She is a Certified Public Accountant.








 




Richard D. Sieradzki



Title: Chief Accounting Officer
Email Address: RSieradzki@Synalloy.com



Richard D. Sieradzki  joined the Company in 2007 and was named Chief Accounting Officer in July 2015.   Mr. Sieradzki has held several positions within the Company including Chief Financial Officer and Vice President, Finance. Prior to joining the Company, he was employed by Buffets, Inc. – Ryan’s Division as Divisional Vice President, Finance from 2006 to 2007 and from 1988 to 2006, he was Vice President, Accounting and Corporate Controller at Ryan’s Restaurant Group, Inc. Mr. Sieradzki received his B. S. degree from Indiana University at South Bend.  He is a Certified Public Accountant.








 




Mandi K. Blagg



Title: Corporate Controller
Email Address: MBlagg@Synalloy.com



Mandi K. Blagg joined the Company in 2011 and was named Corporate Controller in January 2014.  She began her career and spent six years in public accounting, specializing in the external audits of manufacturing companies, governmental and special purpose entities, and employee benefit plans. Ms. Blagg received her B.B.A. in Accounting and Master of Accountancy from the University of Georgia, graduating Cum Laude.  She is a Certified Public Accountant.








 




Chris T. Campbell



Title: Director of Compliance and Controls
Email Address: CCampbell@Synalloy.com



Chris T. Campbell joined the Company in July 2016 as Director of Compliance and Controls. Prior to Synalloy, he served for four years as the Chief Audit Executive for Ntelos Holdings Corporation (NASDAQ: NTLS) and for thirteen years in the Corporate Audit function of Capital One (NYSE: COF). Mr. Campbell began his career at Pricewaterhouse Coopers.  He has a broad background in internal audit, SOX compliance, ethics and fraud investigations, and enterprise risk management practices, spanning several industries. Mr. Campbell received his B.B.A in Accounting from James Madison University.  He is a Certified Public Accountant.








 




Michael Padden



Title: Corporate Director of IT
Email Address: MPadden@Synalloy.com



Michael Padden joined the Company in 2012 as the  Corporate Director of IT.  Prior to Synalloy, he had a 13 year tenure with the Smithfield Packing Company where he held a variety of positions within IT until his last assignment as Director of IT. Mr. Padden received his B.S.B.A. in Management of Information Systems from East Carolina University.








 




Robby Peay



Title: General Counsel
Email Address: RPeay@Synalloy.com



Mr. Peay became General Counsel of Synalloy in 2012. Prior to joining Synalloy, Robby managed a privately held business from 2008 to 2012 and, prior to that experience, worked as a mergers and acquisitions attorney for two prominent Virginia-based law firms. Mr. Peay holds a B.A. from Hampden-Sydney College, where he played varsity baseball, a J.D. from the University of Richmond, and a M.B.A. from the University of Richmond.








 




Greg Gibson



Title: President, Synalloy Chemicals
Email Address: GGibson@Synalloy.com



Greg Gibson was named President, Synalloy Chemicals in April 2015, with business unit responsibility for both Manufacturers Chemicals and CRI Tolling.  Previously, he served as Executive Vice President, Sales and Administration for Manufacturers Chemicals from 2011 to 2015 and held various sales roles at Manufacturers Chemicals from 2005 to 2011.   Mr. Gibson has many years of experience in both the pharmaceutical and chemical industries and proven expertise in building client relationships, growing product market share, sales profitability and developing and executing sales strategies.  Mr. Gibson graduated with a Bachelor of Science Degree from the University of Tennessee at Chattanooga and an MBA from the University of North Alabama.








 




J. Kyle Pennington



Title: President, Synalloy Metals
Email Address: KPennington@Brismet.com



Kyle Pennington was named President, Synalloy Metals in January 2013, with business unit responsibility for Bristol Metals, Palmer of Texas and Specialty Pipe & Tube.  Previously, Mr. Pennington served as President, Bristol Metals from July 2011 until December 2012; President, Bristol Metals’ BRISMET Pipe Division from September 2009 to July 2011; and Vice President, Manufacturing, Bristol Metals from December 2007 through September 2009. Prior to joining the Company, Mr. Pennington worked for 17 years in the metals industry including 12 years’ experience in executive management and service on the Board of Directors of Texas & Northern Industries, a Lone Star Steel Company subsidiary. He received his B.S. in Business Management degree from the University of Tennessee.








 




John C. Tidlow



Title: Executive Vice President, Synalloy Metals
Email Address: JTidlow@SynalloyMetals.com



John C. Tidlow joined Bristol Metals in October 2001. He currently serves as Executive Vice President, Synalloy Metals. Previously, Mr. Tidlow served as Vice President of Marketing and Planning, Vice President of Purchasing and General Manager of Fabrication. Mr. Tidlow received his B.A. in Economics from the University of Pennsylvania and an M.B.A from Villanova University.








 




Steven Baroff



Title: President, Specialty Pipe & Tube, a division of Synalloy Metals
Email Address: SBaroff@SpecialtyPipe.com



Mr. Baroff has served as President of Specialty Pipe & Tube since March 2001. Previously, he served as Vice President Sales and Marketing and has over 30 years experience in the master distribution of heavy wall carbon steel pipe and tubing. Mr. Baroff received his B.A. in Finance from University of Florida.














